            <h2 class="page-title">How to Care for Your Cat</h2>
            
            <div class="care-content">
                <p>While cats may seem self-sufficient, proper care is essential for their health and happiness. Here are some key info for your feline care:</p>
                
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Nutrition:</strong> Provide high-quality cat food depending on your cat's age, weight, and health status. Always keep fresh water available in clean bowls.</li>
                    <li><strong>Litter Box Maintenance:</strong> Place litter boxes in quiet, accessible locations and clean them daily. Most cats prefer unscented litter in a spacious box.</li>
                    <li><strong>Exercise and Enrichment:</strong> Stimulate your cat through interactive toys, climbing trees, and play sessions. This helps prevent obesity and behavioral issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Comfortable Resting Areas:</strong> Provide various cozy spots for your cat to rest and observe their surroundings. Cats appreciate soft beds, blankets, and elevated perches.</li>
                    <li><strong>Regular Veterinary Care:</strong> Schedule annual check-ups for vaccinations and dental care.</li>
                </ul>
                
